    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stylized motif of the burdock plant, genus Arctium, used in carpet patterns to guard against bad luck or to symbolize abundance. It is a diamond shaped motif, often with a smaller diamond in the middle, of which the distinguishing aspect is the small lines or hooked lines radiating from the outermost diamond to represent small burrs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000132/Suzzallo-UW</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000043881/Landreau and Yohe, Flowers of the Yayla (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gestileerd motief van de klit, geslacht Arctium, dat wordt gebruikt in tapijtpatronen ter bescherming tegen ongeluk of voor het symboliseren van overvloed. Het is een ruitvormig motief, vaak met een kleinere ruit in het midden, waarvan het onderscheidende aspect is dat er kleine lijnen of gebogen lijnen lopen vanuit de buitenste ruit. Deze stellen kleine klitjes voor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>牛蒡屬植物(Arctium)的風格化紋飾，用於地毯圖案中，以驅避厄運，或象徵豐饒。該菱形紋飾中間通常具有較小的菱形，特色是最外圍的菱形，會輻射散出細線條或鉤狀線條，用以代表小毛刺。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
